-- Dish’s Blockbuster Won’t Lengthen Delay on Warner DVD Rentals
-- B y   E d m u n d   L e e
-- 2012-01-10T20:58:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/dish-s-blockbuster-won-t-lengthen-delay-on-warner-dvd-rentals.html
Dish Network Corp. (DISH) ’s Blockbuster
movie-rental chain refused to double a 28-day moratorium on new
DVD rentals from  Warner Bros . and has begun obtaiing the discs
from third-party sources, according to a person with knowledge
of the matter.  Blockbuster stores are now renting Warner Bros. movies on
the day the new DVD is released for sale, said the person, who
wasn’t authorized to speak publicly.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edmund Lee in New York at 
